ðŸ§­ Terraform Project Structure
A typical Terraform project has the following structure:
terraform-project/
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ main.tf          # Main configuration (providers, resources)
â”œâ”€â”€ variables.tf     # Input variables
â”œâ”€â”€ outputs.tf       # Output values
â”œâ”€â”€ terraform.tfvars # Variable values (optional)
â””â”€â”€ versions.tf      # Terraform and provider version constraints


ðŸŒ AWS Terraform Template

versions.tf
terraform {
    required_version = ">= 1.5.0"  
    required_providers {
            aws = {
                    source  = "hashicorp/aws" 
                    version = "~> 5.0"    
                } 
    }
}

main.tf
Terraformprovider "aws" {
    region = var.aws_region
}
# Example resource (can be replaced with any AWS resource)
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "example" {
    bucket = var.bucket_name  
    acl    = "private"
}

variables.tf
variable "aws_region" {
    description = "AWS region to deploy resources"  
    type        = string  
    default     = "us-east-1"
}
variable "bucket_name" {
    description = "Name of the S3 bucket"  
    type        = string
}

terraform.tfvars
Terraformbucket_name = "my-unique-bucket-name-123"

outputs.tf
output "bucket_id" {
    value = aws_s3_bucket.example.id
}


â˜ï¸ Azure Terraform Template

versions.tf
terraform {
    required_version = ">= 1.5.0"  
    required_providers {
        azurerm = {
            source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"      
            version = "~> 3.0"    
        }  
    }
}
provider "azurerm" {
    features {}
}

main.tf
resource "azurerm_resource_group" "example" {
    name     = var.resource_group_name   
    location = var.location
}

variables.tf
variable "resource_group_name" {
    description = "Name of the resource group"  
    type        = string
}
variable "location" {
    description = "Azure region"  
    type        = string 
    default     = "East US"
}

terraform.tfvars

outputs.tf
output "resource_group_id" {
      value = azurerm_resource_group.example.id
}      


ðŸš€ Terraform Workflow Steps

Initialize Terraform:
terraform init

Validate Configuration:
terraform validate

Preview Changes:
terraform plan

Apply Changes:
terraform apply

Destroy Resources (optional):
terraform destroy